Solid Primitives for Automerge Repo
===================================

These hooks are provided as helpers for using Automerge in your Solid project.

<RepoProvider repo={Repo}/>
---------------------------
Wrapper context required in Automerge Solid apps

useRepo(): Repo
---------------
Get a direct reference to the current repo.

useHandle<T>(() => AnyDocumentId): Handle
------------------------------
Get a handle from the repo.

useDocument<T>(() => AnyDocumentId): [T, (fn: changeFn<T>) => void]
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Get a document and change function from the repo.

createDocumentStore(() => Handle): [doc, (fn: changeFn<T>) => void]
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a naïve* deeply-reactive solid store wrapper for a handle

useDocumentStore<T>(() => AnyDocumentId): [T, (fn: changeFn<T>) => void]
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Get a naïve* deeply-reactive solid store from the repo

*naïve: this only supports simple docs made of simple pojo values. not rich text
or conflicts.
